.TH _PRINTF 3 "2025-10-02" "holbertonschool-printf" "_printf manual"
.SH NAME
_printf \- produce output according to a format (mini printf)
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B #include "main.h"
.br
.B int _printf(const char *format, ...);
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B _printf()
prints output to the standard output stream (file descriptor 1)
according to a format string. It is a simplified reimplementation
of the C library
.BR printf (3)
and supports a subset of conversion specifiers.

The
.I format
string is composed of ordinary characters, which are copied
verbatim to the output, and conversion directives which start with
a percent sign (%). Each directive specifies how to convert the next
argument from the variadic argument list.

This project version does
not handle flags, field width, precision, or length modifiers.

.SH SUPPORTED CONVERSIONS
.TP
.B %c
Print a single character. Argument type: (int).
.TP
.B %s
Print a C string. Argument type: (char *). If the pointer is NULL,
"(null)" is printed.
.TP
.B %%
Print a literal percent sign.
.TP
.B %d
Print a signed decimal integer. Argument type: (int).
.TP
.B %i
Alias of %d. Argument type: (int).

.SH RETURN VALUE
On success,
.B _printf()
returns the total number of characters written (excluding the
terminating null byte). On error, it returns \-1.

.SH ERRORS
.TP
.B EINVAL
Returned as \-1 when:
.RS
.IP \(bu 2
format is NULL.
.IP \(bu 2
format is exactly "%", i.e., a trailing percent with no specifier.
.RE

.SH NOTES
This implementation writes characters using
.BR write (2)
(indirectly via a helper like
.BR _putchar ),
does not allocate dynamic buffers, and avoids using the standard
library
.BR printf (3)
internally. It handles INT_MIN safely by promoting to long before
conversion to unsigned.

.SH EXAMPLES
.nf
/* Print strings and numbers */
_printf("Hello %s! num=%d%%\\n", "World", 42);

/* Characters and signed integers */
_printf("char: %c, pos: %d, neg: %i\\n", 'A', 123, -456);

/* Null string handling */
_printf("s: %s\\n", (char *)0);  /* prints: s: (null) */
.fi

Expected output:
.nf
Hello World! num=42%
char: A, pos: 123, neg: -456
s: (null)
.fi

.SH SEE ALSO
.BR printf (3),
.BR write (2)

.SH AUTHOR
Abdullah Mushabab Alsalem
Sondos Saleh Alrubaish

.SH VERSION
Task 2 man page for simplified _printf (supports %c, %s, %%, %d, %i).
